# Table Support in Notedown

This sample demonstrates the table feature in Notedown.

## Basic Table

| Header 1 | Header 2 | Header 3 |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| Row 1    | Data     | Value    |
| Row 2    | Data     | Value    |

## Table with Alignment

| Left-aligned | Center-aligned | Right-aligned |
| :----------- | :------------: | ------------: |
| Left         | Center         | Right         |
| Column       | Column         | Column        |

## Table with Formatting

| Format Type | Example                                    |
| ----------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| **Bold**    | This text is in **bold**.                  |
| *Italic*    | This text is in *italic*.                  |
| `Code`      | This is `inline code`.                     |
| Links       | This is a [link to Google](https://google.com). |

## Table with Meta References

| Property | Value         |
| -------- | ------------- |
| Title    | @{title}      |
| Author   | @{author}     |
| Count    | 3 tables      |

## Complex Table Example

| Feature | Description | Support | Example |
| ------- | ----------- | :-----: | ------- |
| Headers | Table headers | ✅ | The first row |
| Alignment | Text alignment | ✅ | Left, center, right |
| Formatting | Text styling | ✅ | **Bold**, *Italic* |
| Meta Refs | Variable references | ✅ | @{title} |
| LaTeX | Math formulas | ✅ | $E = mc^2$ |
